thread.title_full: One dead in tree fall in Mumbai's Mulund - The Times of India

author: Richa Pinto
title: One dead in tree fall in Mumbai's Mulund
text:
MUMBAI: Another 65 year old man lost his life after a tree fell over him at Mulund on Tuesday evening. This follows four deaths which had taken place on account of tree collapse on Monday at Santacruz. Two others were injured in the incident at Mulund.
Shadashiv Sawant (65) died after a tree crashed on a footwear stall at Nani Pada Road Apna Bazar Fatak in Mulund (east). Two others were injured off which one was sent to Sion hospital.
On Monday four people died and five others were injured at Vakola after a tree fell over a wall which then crashed into a make shift hutment adjacent to it. At 2.57am on Monday, a huge tree located in a private building fell over a wall which crashed into a hut.
